&lt;h1&gt;Heart Failure Specialist Nurse - Band 7&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent opportunity for a nurse with evidence of broad cardiology experience to work in this specialist field. These are exciting times as we expand our service. You’ll be supported by Consultant colleagues as we grow an enthusiastic, flexible and dynamic team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This diverse role involves working closely with medical and nursing teams, teaching patients and their families and liaising with staff in the community. You’ll be required to work autonomously prioritising and managing patients with acute, chronic and end of life care needs, within hospital and the hospital clinic setting. Experience of heart failure is preferred in order to support specialist clinical management, through to safe discharge, both within Cardiology and across the wider Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post requires advanced clinical assessment skills, non- medical prescribing and excellent communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information or an informal visit please contact Catriona Glen or Cath Fee, Heart Failure Specialist Nurse’s Catrionaglen@nhs.net Catherine.fee@nhs.net 01225 825587, bleep 7717&lt;/p&gt;
